    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dear Mr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>I have to ask you on<lb/> behalf of our President and Trustees to repeat<lb/> your paper on the &#34;Alliance&#34;¬ù before our con&#45;<lb/>gregation any evening next week you choose.<lb/></p>
            <p>The formal official invitation will<lb/> be forwarded you Sunday. But I write now<lb/> in order that I may have your reply by Monday<lb/> and to have time to get notices printed to<lb/> send to our members. I would suggest Thursday.<lb/></p>
            <p>My object is 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> that our Congregation<lb/> may be the first to be in the field for the Alliance<lb/> just as I made it take the initiative in starting<lb/> the Montefiore Home.<lb/></p>
            <p>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>. To repeat my own paper<lb/> in the hope that what I say in it may induce<lb/> a little more activity in my own congregation in<lb/> the way I suggest therein.<lb/></p>
            <p>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> and chiefly. To bring you before<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the congregation and let the folks see what an or&#45;<lb/>nament orthodoxy has&#44; whose only fault is being over&#45;<lb/> modest.<lb/></p>
            <p>I trust you will accept the invitation. I will<lb/> come to Phil<hi rend="sup">phia</hi> to officially escort you as<lb/> the guest of my Community of Remnants &#40;&#91;Hebrew&#93;&#41;<lb/></p>
            <p>With regards<lb/>
                Yrs vy try&#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/>
                H Pereira Mendes<lb/></p>
            <p>313W30<lb/>
                23 Jan85<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
